3. cs.DS - The paper uses argumentation frameworks, which can be represented as graphs, and thus can be studied using graph theory, a subfield of computer science. 
4. cs.MA - The paper deals with multi-agent systems, as argumentation theory is often used to model conflicting information among multiple agents.
